# Frontend Coding Rules

## Purpose

This file defines the coding standards for implementing frontend code that is consistent with the design system. These rules govern **how** design tokens, components, and patterns are expressed in code. They complement the design system documentation rules (`design-system.mdc`) by specifying the code-level requirements.

These rules apply to all web frontend code, regardless of the framework (React, Next.js, Vue, etc.). Framework-specific notes are provided where relevant.

> **AI Instruction**: Apply these rules to ALL frontend code you write. When reviewing existing frontend code, note violations and fix them when the file is in scope. Before writing any frontend code, read `docs/design-system/LLM-QUICKREF.md` as your primary reference.

---

## Token Usage in Code

### Rule FE-001: No Hardcoded Visual Values

Never hardcode visual values in frontend code. All colors, typography, spacing, border radii, shadows, and motion values must reference design system tokens.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Uses design system tokens
<div className="text-body text-text-primary bg-surface border border-border-default p-4 rounded-md">
  Content
</div>

// CORRECT: CSS variable reference
const styles = {
  color: 'var(--text-primary)',
  padding: 'var(--space-4)',
  borderRadius: 'var(--radius-md)',
};

// INCORRECT: Hardcoded values
<div style={{ color: '#1A1A2E', padding: '16px', fontSize: '14px' }}>
  Content
</div>

// INCORRECT: Magic numbers
<div className="p-[13px] text-[15px] rounded-[6px]">
  Content
</div>
```

**Prohibited in any frontend file**:
- Hex color codes (`#RRGGBB`, `#RGB`)
- RGB/HSL color functions (`rgb()`, `hsl()`) unless referencing CSS variables internally
- Raw pixel values that do not map to a spacing scale step
- Arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., `p-[13px]`, `text-[15px]`, `w-[320px]`) unless explicitly approved in a design system document
- CSS color names (`red`, `blue`, `gray`) in styles

### Rule FE-002: Font Weight Constraint

Only two font weights are permitted: **400 (regular)** and **500 (medium)**. No other weight shall appear anywhere in the codebase.

```tsx
// CORRECT
<h2 className="font-medium">Section Title</h2>
<p className="font-normal">Body text</p>

// INCORRECT
<h1 className="font-bold">Title</h1>      // 700 — prohibited
<span className="font-semibold">Label</span> // 600 — prohibited
<p className="font-light">Caption</p>     // 300 — prohibited
```

**In CSS/Tailwind config**: only `fontWeight: { normal: '400', medium: '500' }` should appear in the font weight scale.

### Rule FE-003: Spacing Scale Compliance

All spacing must use values from the design system spacing scale. Do not use arbitrary pixel values for `margin`, `padding`, `gap`, `width`, or `height` when the intent is to follow the spacing system.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Spacing scale values
<div className="p-4 gap-6 mt-8">          // 16px, 24px, 32px — on-scale
  <div className="mb-3">...</div>         // 12px — on-scale
</div>

// INCORRECT: Off-scale values
<div className="p-[13px] gap-[18px]">    // 13px, 18px — not on the scale
  <div style={{ marginBottom: '10px' }}>  // 10px — not on the scale
  </div>
</div>
```

**Exception**: pixel-perfect values required by third-party library constraints may use arbitrary values only if documented in the component record.

### Rule FE-004: Semantic Token Priority

Components must reference **semantic tokens** (Level 2) or **pillar tokens** (Level 3), never primitive tokens (Level 1) directly. Semantic tokens encode purpose; primitive tokens encode raw values.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Semantic token
className="bg-surface text-text-primary border-border-default"
// or via CSS variable: var(--bg-surface), var(--text-primary)

// INCORRECT: Primitive token used directly
className="bg-neutral-100 text-neutral-900"
// or via CSS variable: var(--color-neutral-100)
```

