## Component Implementation

### Rule FE-005: All Interactive States Are Required

Every interactive component must implement all applicable states defined in DS-009. A component that only handles the default and hover states is incomplete. States must be visually distinct and accessible.

**Required states checklist** for interactive components:

| State | Implementation requirement |
|---|---|
| Default | Base styles, fully functional |
| Hover | Visual change indicating interactivity (`cursor-pointer`, color shift) |
| Focus | Visible focus ring — minimum 2px, uses `--focus-ring` token or equivalent, 3:1 contrast |
| Active/Pressed | Visual depression or feedback |
| Disabled | `disabled` or `aria-disabled="true"`, visual distinction beyond opacity alone, non-interactive |
| Loading | Spinner or skeleton, `aria-busy="true"`, prevents re-submission |
| Error | Error color + error icon + error text — never color alone |
| Success | Success color + success icon + confirmation text (where applicable) |
| Selected | Uses `--bg-selected` token, visually distinct from default |

```tsx
// CORRECT: Button with all states
<button
  disabled={isDisabled}
  aria-busy={isLoading}
  className={cn(
    // Default
    "px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-sm font-medium",
    "bg-action-primary text-text-inverse",
    // Hover
    "hover:bg-action-primary-hover",
    // Focus
    "focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-focus-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2",
    // Active
    "active:bg-action-primary-active",
    // Disabled
    "disabled:bg-action-disabled disabled:text-text-disabled disabled:cursor-not-allowed",
    // Loading
    isLoading && "opacity-75 cursor-wait",
  )}
>
  {isLoading ? <Spinner aria-hidden="true" /> : null}
  {children}
</button>

// INCORRECT: Only default and hover, focus ring missing
<button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 px-4 py-2">
  {children}
</button>
```

### Rule FE-006: Component File Structure

Frontend component files follow a consistent structure:

```tsx
// 1. Imports (grouped: React → third-party → local → types)
import React from 'react';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import { Icon } from '@/components/ui/icon';
import type { ButtonProps } from './button.types';

// 2. Type definitions (if not in separate .types.ts file)
interface Props { ... }

// 3. Component function
export function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2, ...rest }: Props) {
  // 3a. State and derived values
  // 3b. Event handlers
  // 3c. Effects (if any)
  // 3d. Render
  return ( ... );
}

// 4. Display name (for dev tools)
ComponentName.displayName = 'ComponentName';
```

**Naming**:
- Component files: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `data-table.tsx`)
- Component exports: `PascalCase` (e.g., `DataTable`)
- Variant-specific files: `component-name--variant.tsx` (only when variant is truly separate)

### Rule FE-007: No Custom Re-implementations of Library Components

If a component exists in the design system component library (`docs/design-system/COMPONENT-LIBRARY.md`), use it. Do not create a custom implementation that duplicates its function.

If the existing component does not support a needed use case:
1. Check whether a documented variant covers it
2. If not, propose a new variant via `/08d` and implement after design system is updated
3. Temporary deviations must be documented in the component record

```tsx
// CORRECT: Uses the design system Alert component
import { Alert } from '@/components/ui/alert';
<Alert variant="warning" title="Heads up">...</Alert>

// INCORRECT: Custom warning implementation
<div className="bg-yellow-100 border border-yellow-300 p-4 rounded">
  <span className="font-semibold">Heads up:</span> ...
</div>
```

