## Loading, Empty, and Error States

### Rule FE-008: Skeleton Loading Over Generic Spinners

For content with a predictable layout, loading states must use skeleton components that mirror the expected content shape. Generic full-page spinners are only acceptable when the content layout cannot be predicted.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Skeleton mirrors content
{isLoading ? (
  <div className="space-y-3">
    <Skeleton className="h-6 w-3/4" />
    <Skeleton className="h-4 w-full" />
    <Skeleton className="h-4 w-5/6" />
  </div>
) : (
  <ArticleContent title={data.title} body={data.body} />
)}

// INCORRECT: Generic spinner for structured content
{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : <ArticleContent ... />}
```

### Rule FE-009: Empty States Are Not Optional

Any data view that can return zero items must have a designed empty state. A blank container or a cryptic "No data" message is not acceptable.

Empty states must include:
- An icon or illustration relevant to the content type
- A message explaining why the view is empty (or that it is empty)
- A call to action when applicable (e.g., "Create your first pipeline")

```tsx
// CORRECT: Meaningful empty state
{items.length === 0 ? (
  <EmptyState
    icon={<PipelineIcon className="w-12 h-12 text-text-disabled" />}
    title="No pipelines yet"
    description="Create your first pipeline to start processing data."
    action={<Button onClick={onCreateClick}>Create pipeline</Button>}
  />
) : (
  <PipelineList items={items} />
)}

// INCORRECT: Blank container or bare text
{items.length === 0 ? <p>No data</p> : <PipelineList ... />}
```

### Rule FE-010: Error States Must Be Actionable

Error states must tell the user what went wrong and what they can do about it. Error messages must use the error semantic color token, an error icon, and descriptive text — never color alone.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Actionable error with color + icon + text
{error ? (
  <ErrorState
    icon={<AlertCircleIcon className="text-error" aria-hidden="true" />}
    title="Could not load pipelines"
    description={error.message}
    action={<Button variant="secondary" onClick={onRetry}>Try again</Button>}
  />
) : ...}

// INCORRECT: Color-only error indicator
{error ? <div className="bg-red-50 text-red-500">Error occurred</div> : ...}
```

