## Page Archetypes

### Rule FE-014: Every Page Must Use a Page Archetype

Before implementing a new page, classify it using the archetypes in `docs/design-system/PAGE-ARCHETYPES.md`. The archetype determines the layout structure, information density, and responsive behavior.

```tsx
// In the component record or implementation notes, document:
// Archetype: #4 Dashboard — "Metrics and recent activity"
// Deviations: None

// If no archetype fits, compose from the nearest match and document:
// Archetype: Composite — #6 Entity Detail + #4 Dashboard sections
// Rationale: [explanation]
```

If a page does not fit any existing archetype, document the deviation in the component record and propose a new archetype via `/08d`.

### Rule FE-015: Layout Composition Using Archetype Templates

When implementing a page, start from the archetype's layout template (if defined in `PAGE-ARCHETYPES.md`) before adding content-specific elements. Do not build layouts from scratch if an archetype applies.

