## Content Rendering

### Rule FE-021: Authored Content Uses Content Rendering Rules

When rendering authored content (articles, tutorials, documentation), apply the content rendering rules from `docs/design-system/CONTENT-RENDERING.md` rather than the UI chrome styles.

```tsx
// CORRECT: Authored content wrapped in content renderer
<ContentRenderer className="prose-syntropy">
  {article.body}
</ContentRenderer>

// INCORRECT: Applying UI chrome styles to article content
<div className="text-body text-text-primary">
  {article.body} // Will have UI density, not reading-optimized density
</div>
```

Authored content has different typographic rules: larger line height (1.7), more generous paragraph spacing, reading-optimized max-width, and heading spacing as defined in the content rendering document.

