## Anti-Patterns

### Rule FE-022: Prohibited Anti-Patterns Checklist

The following are prohibited in all frontend code:

| Anti-Pattern | Prohibition | Correct Alternative |
|---|---|---|
| Hardcoded hex colors | FE-001 | Use semantic CSS variable token |
| Font weight ≠ 400 or 500 | FE-002 | Use `font-normal` or `font-medium` |
| Off-scale spacing | FE-003 | Use spacing scale tokens |
| Primitive token in component | FE-004 | Use semantic token |
| Missing focus ring | FE-005 | `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-focus-ring` |
| Generic spinner for structured content | FE-008 | Skeleton matching content shape |
| Blank container as "empty state" | FE-009 | EmptyState component with message + CTA |
| Color-only error indicator | FE-010 | Error color + icon + text |
| Desktop-first responsive | FE-011 | Mobile-first with breakpoint prefixes |
| Custom breakpoints | FE-012 | Use design system breakpoints only |
| Re-implementing library components | FE-007 | Use the component from the library |
| Glass morphism (unless DS-approved) | FE-001, DS-016 | Use elevation shadow tokens |
| `backdrop-filter: blur` without DS approval | FE-001, DS-016 | Use solid background tokens |
| `position: fixed` overlays without focus trap | FE-017 | Implement focus trap in modals/dialogs |
| Pillar-specific colors hardcoded in components | FE-019 | Use `--pillar-accent` token |
| Overriding `--action-primary` per pillar | FE-020 | Pillar accent ≠ primary action |

